 an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue   Lexington  VA 24450 P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 463 2695 give vmiaa org Why Give   Giving Priorities  skip to content VMI VMI Alumni Keydet Club Webcams Directories Login Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give Close Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org   Strengthen Academics Programs  Faculty  FacilitiesState of the art facilities  small classes  academic support  honors and leadership programming   strong academics come only from strong support for all areas of the VMI education  Learn More   Prepare Leaders Corps LifeMaintaining equipment and facilities  and providing coaches  TAC officers  and other staff  are essential to the life of the Corps  Support of Corps Life is an investment in graduates who serve and lead with honor and integrity  Learn More   Support the Team NCAA AthleticsSupport of VMI athletics is support for a strong and diverse athletic program that builds physical fitness and imparts lifelong lessons in character  discipline  and teamwork  Learn More   Provide Opportunity Scholarship   AidWhether athletic or academic  scholarships offer young people the opportunity to embrace academic rigor coupled with a commitment to honor  duty  and professionalism  Learn More   Believe in the Mission Unrestricted SupportAs we celebrate